column5: Ordered a subscription to Ontario Outdoors a month ago abouts. With the deal came a ice fishing rod and foldable fillet knife. Not bad for free I guess. It's not Cadallic stuff, but hey Jack I don't need no Cadallic stuff lol. The knife I know nothing about, but the rod they sent is a Berkley light action and already spooled. I think ill be double fistin this winter  Good magazine as well. Lots of interesting stuff.
Looks like a decent little ice rod for the price ! Haha  Actually I have the older version of that combo, I believe. The reel bit the dust after a season, but hey, I paid for mine!
Coast makes good equipment, and OOD is obviously an awesome mag.
Reels a cheapy 1 bearing, and I can feel the resistance while rotating it, but ill put it to good use.
Cheapie reel, test the drag before heading out
